Text:
Be it enacted by the Council as follows:

	Section 1.   Subdivision a of section 27-353.1 of the administrative code of the city of New York is REPEALED and subdivision b and c of such section are relettered to be subdivision a and b.
	�2.	The heading of section 27-353.1 of such code is amended to read as follows:
	�27-353.1  Smoke protection for [elevators and] escalators.
	�3.	Subdivision w of section 27-954 of such code is amended to read as follows:
	(w)	In all existing buildings classified in occupancy group J-1 [(except for "residential hotels," as such term is defined by the commissioner pursuant to rules and regulations) all]:
	(1)	All spaces listed in subdivisions (c), (d), (l), (m), (n), (o), (p) and (q), [,] of this section, except that an approved smoke detection alarm system may be installed in those locations described under subdivisions (o) and (q) in lieu of sprinklers.  Such smoke detection system shall be of the supervisory type connected to an approval central station; and
	(2)	All corridors, public areas, storage closets and spaces in occupancy groups C and F; or all sleeping rooms, storage closets and spaces in occupancy groups C and F;
	(3)	Sprinklers required by paragraph (2) of this subdivision may be omitted at every floor above the main entrance floor where all elevators open only into elevator vestibules that have been completed on or before April first, nineteen hundred eighty-seven;
	(4)	Notwithstanding paragraph (2) of this subdivision, storage closets with an area of less than seventy-five square feet may be provided with smoke detectors of the central supervisory type connected to an approved central station;
	(5)	Notwithstanding any other provision of this code, the sprinklers serving the storage closets may be connected with the domestic water supply;
	(6)	Notwithstanding paragraph (2) of this subdivision, in all existing buildings classified in occupancy group J-1, a system of automatic sprinklers shall be required throughout all areas of such buildings;
	(7)	(A)	Buildings and spaces subject to the requirements of paragraph (2) of this subdivision shall be in compliance therewith on or before December thirty-first, nineteen hundred eighty-nine;
		(B)	Buildings subject to the requirements of paragraph (6) of this subdivision shall be in compliance therewith on or before December thirty-first, nineteen hundred eight-nine;
	(8)	Notwithstanding paragraphs (6) and (7) of this subdivision, where compliance with the time requirements set forth in such paragraphs would cause undue hardship, the commissioner, with the approval of the fire commissioner, may extend the time of compliance.  Before an application for such a time extension shall be considered, all required applications and plans shall be filed and approved, permits obtained and a good faith effort towards completion of the work shall have been made.
	�4.	Such section of such code is amended by adding a new subdivision (a) to read as follows:
	(a)	Sprinklers for escalators, where required by article five of subchapter five of this code.
	�5.	This local law shall take effect immediately, except as otherwise specifically provided herein.
